00:30:39,157 --> 00:30:42,058
He give you a very nice
lacquered cup, boss.

459
00:30:42,227 --> 00:30:43,626
He make that cup hisself.

460
00:30:43,795 --> 00:30:45,786
No, he didn't.
Well, you thank him for me...

461
00:30:45,964 --> 00:30:49,957
...and tell him that I'll be forever indebted
to him for his very lovely gift.

462
00:30:50,135 --> 00:30:52,069
You are most welcome, captain.

463
00:30:52,537 --> 00:30:54,528
Hey, you speak English.

464
00:30:54,706 --> 00:30:58,733
Sure, boss, Mr. Oshira teach me
English when I'm a little boy in Tobiki.

465
00:30:58,910 --> 00:31:02,141
- How do you like...?
- In my youth, I work in Manila.

466
00:31:02,313 --> 00:31:04,873
How is Mr. McKinley?

467
00:31:05,050 --> 00:31:07,041
Oh, you mean President McKinley?

468
00:31:07,218 --> 00:31:08,981
Well, I'm afraid somebody shot him.

469
00:31:09,154 --> 00:31:11,679
- I am sorry.
- Well, it was a long time ago, you know.

470
00:31:12,123 --> 00:31:14,216
Yes, a long time.

471
00:31:14,592 --> 00:31:17,322
May August moon fill your cup.

472
00:31:17,495 --> 00:31:19,224
Why an August moon, sir?

473
00:31:19,397 --> 00:31:25,302
All moons good, but August
moon little older, little wiser.

474
00:31:25,470 --> 00:31:29,201
Is it...? Sakini said that you
made this cup all by yourself.

475
00:31:29,374 --> 00:31:32,207
- Oh, yes.
- You know that this is a lost art, Sakini.

476
00:31:32,377 --> 00:31:36,438
This is an industry we could start
right here, right now in Tobiki.

477
00:31:36,614 --> 00:31:39,310
- Think you could mass-produce these?
- Mass-produce?

478
00:31:39,484 --> 00:31:42,317
Yes, you know, set up machines,
turn them out by the gross.

479
00:31:43,288 --> 00:31:47,452
I take pride in making
one cup at a time, captain.

480
00:31:47,625 --> 00:31:50,651
How many do you think
you could turn out in, oh, say, one day?

481
00:31:51,162 --> 00:31:56,099
If I work hard,
maybe one or two a week.

482
00:31:56,501 --> 00:31:58,731
Fine, that's good,
you make as many as you can.

483
00:31:58,903 --> 00:32:00,700
We'll send them up
to the Post Exchange.

484
00:32:00,872 --> 00:32:03,033
And sell them as fast
as you can turn them out.

485
00:32:03,208 --> 00:32:04,641
I shall do my best.

486
00:32:05,043 --> 00:32:08,774
Fine. We're in business. Now, Mr. Hokaida,
you make those cricket cages...

487
00:32:08,947 --> 00:32:11,279
...and the getas, fine,
we can sell a lot of those.

488
00:32:11,449 --> 00:32:13,542
And the chopsticks, great.
A lot of those.

489
00:32:13,718 --> 00:32:17,586
And I saw some straw hats.
See those straw hats? Make a lot of those.

490
00:32:17,755 --> 00:32:20,053
We're going into
the souvenir business, folks.

491
00:32:20,225 --> 00:32:21,453
We gonna make money, boss?

492
00:32:21,626 --> 00:32:23,856
Make enough of these,
I'll guarantee recovery...

493
00:32:24,028 --> 00:32:26,496
...of Tobiki village. You tell them that.

494
00:32:29,801 --> 00:32:33,168
Oh, boss, you very big success.
They sure like you already, boss.

495
00:32:33,338 --> 00:32:35,898
And they say they will make
everything fast as dickens.

496
00:32:36,074 --> 00:32:38,474
Sakini, ask them to postpone
any more gifts for now.

497
00:32:38,643 --> 00:32:40,907
I wanna tell them
what we're going to do for them.

498
00:32:41,079 --> 00:32:42,205
Okay.

499
00:32:44,549 --> 00:32:45,777
What?

500
00:32:46,784 --> 00:32:50,743
Okay. They say okay, boss. They got
no more presents for you anyhow.

501
00:32:50,922 --> 00:32:53,482
It's important that I tell them
about the schoolhouse...

502
00:32:53,658 --> 00:32:55,717
...that we'll build for their children.

503
00:32:55,894 --> 00:32:59,921
Now, according to plan B, I believe it says
the direct approach is the most effective.

504
00:33:00,098 --> 00:33:02,760
- So you ready?
- Oh, all set, boss.

505
00:33:02,934 --> 00:33:04,834
Do you want to be ignorant?

506
00:33:07,705 --> 00:33:09,730
- What? What was that?
- They say yes, boss.

507
00:33:09,908 --> 00:33:12,775
Yes? You mean they
want to be ignorant?

508
00:33:12,944 --> 00:33:16,277
Oh, no, boss. Oh, in Japanese, boss,
yes mean no.

509
00:33:16,447 --> 00:33:19,211
They say, "Yes, we not
want to be ignorant."

510
00:33:19,384 --> 00:33:21,818
Oh, I see.

511
00:33:21,986 --> 00:33:24,853
Do you want your children
to be ignorant?

512
00:33:28,326 --> 00:33:29,554
Now, what was that?

513
00:33:29,727 --> 00:33:31,922
They say no, boss.

514
00:33:32,096 --> 00:33:33,563
No? Wait a minute now.

515
00:33:33,731 --> 00:33:35,631
Sakini, no, they do? Or no, they don't?

516
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:39,099
Yes, boss. They not want
no ignorant children.

517
00:33:39,270 --> 00:33:40,931
Right. Now...

518
00:33:41,105 --> 00:33:45,667
...there's gonna be a daily issue
of rice for everybody here.

519
00:33:48,813 --> 00:33:52,044
Yes, yes. And we're gonna build
a fine new schoolhouse...

520
00:33:52,217 --> 00:33:54,185
...for your children.

521
00:33:54,852 --> 00:33:57,286
Wait. Pentagon-shaped.

522
00:34:00,658 --> 00:34:02,353
Pentagon.

523
00:34:03,428 --> 00:34:04,759
Pentagon.

524
00:34:05,296 --> 00:34:08,288
She say, "What is a pentagon?"
Boss, they never hear before.

525
00:34:08,466 --> 00:34:10,331
They've never heard of the Pentagon?

526
00:34:10,501 --> 00:34:12,765
- No, boss.
- They certainly do need a school here.

527
00:34:12,937 --> 00:34:15,064
Pentagon. Everybody knows
what the Pentagon is.

528
00:34:15,240 --> 00:34:18,641
The P... It's...

529
00:34:18,810 --> 00:34:22,143
Well, it really means
five-sided, you know, Sakini.

530
00:34:22,313 --> 00:34:24,611
- Five-sided?
- Yes, it has five si...

531
00:34:38,863 --> 00:34:42,890
They say... Boss, they say there are no
children in Tobiki got the five sides.

532
00:34:43,067 --> 00:34:45,058
No, no, the school.

533
00:34:45,236 --> 00:34:48,296
The school has five sides,
not the children. I mean, not in re...

534
00:34:48,473 --> 00:34:51,033
No, you see, it's like a building
in Washington, folks.

535
00:34:51,209 --> 00:34:54,406
And everybody is gonna
learn about democracy.

536
00:34:59,717 --> 00:35:03,209
They say, "What is a democracy?" boss.
They know what rice is.

537
00:35:03,388 --> 00:35:07,051
Yes, all right. Democracy is a
system of self-determination.

538
00:35:07,225 --> 00:35:10,422
It's the... It's the right
to make the wrong choice.

539
00:35:14,966 --> 00:35:17,196
Wait a minute, we're not
getting through to them.

540
00:35:17,368 --> 00:35:18,596
Let me explain it this way.

541
00:35:18,770 --> 00:35:22,706
Suppose I'm back home and I don't like
the way that Uncle Sam is treating me.

542
00:35:22,874 --> 00:35:24,603
Well, do you know what I can do?

543
00:35:24,776 --> 00:35:28,644
I can write to the president himself,
and I can tell him so.

544
00:35:34,485 --> 00:35:38,421
They say, "But do you send
that letter?" boss.

545
00:35:39,090 --> 00:35:40,990
- Let's get on with the lecture now.
- Okay.

546
00:35:41,159 --> 00:35:43,457
Now we'll show you
how democracy really operates.

547
00:35:43,628 --> 00:35:46,290
We'll hold an election.
We're gonna organize this village.

548
00:35:46,464 --> 00:35:48,830
- Is the mayor here?
- Here's the mayor. White coat.

549
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:52,026
We'll have to get him a new coat.
We wouldn't want a new mayor.

550
00:35:52,203 --> 00:35:54,398
Keep the mayor.
Very hard to find a white coat.

551
00:35:54,572 --> 00:35:56,733
We got the mayor.
Now we need a chief of police.

552
00:35:56,908 --> 00:36:00,674
And a chief of agriculture. Now who'd
make a good chief of agriculture here?

553
00:36:06,084 --> 00:36:08,848
They say they like Mr. Seiko.
He the best man for the job.

554
00:36:09,020 --> 00:36:11,250
- He's an experienced farmer?
- He artist, boss.

555
00:36:11,422 --> 00:36:13,720
- What?
- He artist. He draw lovely picture...

556
00:36:13,891 --> 00:36:15,552
...of golden wheat, butterfly...

557
00:36:15,727 --> 00:36:18,662
Sakini, just because he draws
a very nice picture of wheat...

558
00:36:18,830 --> 00:36:21,958
...that doesn't make him
an experienced wheat farmer.

559
00:36:22,133 --> 00:36:25,364
Wheat not grow here anyhow,
just sweet potatoes.

560
00:36:26,504 --> 00:36:30,804
All right. Well, if he's their choice. Fine.
Now, we're gonna have to have...

561
00:36:32,009 --> 00:36:35,308
- What did he say?
- He want a white coat like mayor, boss.

562
00:36:35,480 --> 00:36:39,177
You said that we can't get... That's all right.
If we don't get a white coat...

563
00:36:39,350 --> 00:36:44,287
You know what we'll do? We'll get him
a helmet, and have written on the helmet:

564
00:36:44,455 --> 00:36:46,320
"Chief of agriculture."

565
00:36:49,961 --> 00:36:52,486
Now... Right, fine.
Now, we need a chief of police.

566
00:36:52,663 --> 00:36:55,188
Now, who'd make a good chief
of police?

567
00:36:57,168 --> 00:37:00,501
Hokaida, boss. They say they like
Mr. Hokaida. He champion wrestler.

568
00:37:00,671 --> 00:37:02,662
- They afraid of him.
- Yeah.

569
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:04,330
- That's all right.
- Strong, boss.

570
00:37:04,509 --> 00:37:07,967
Yes, indeed. All right, Fine.
Now we gotta... What?

571
00:37:08,146 --> 00:37:09,670
- What'd he say?
- He want a helmet.

572
00:37:09,847 --> 00:37:12,873
Oh, fine, sure, we'll requisition
a helmet for him too.

573
00:37:13,050 --> 00:37:14,984
All right? Fine. Now for the ladies.

574
00:37:15,153 --> 00:37:16,745
Now, we're gonna organize...

575
00:37:16,921 --> 00:37:18,388
...a... I know what it is...

576
00:37:18,556 --> 00:37:20,922
...it's a Ladies League
for Democratic Action...

577
00:37:21,092 --> 00:37:23,424
...and we're gonna have to
have a league president.

578
00:37:23,594 --> 00:37:25,494
Now, who'd make
a good league president...

579
00:37:25,663 --> 00:37:28,097
...for the Ladies League
for Democratic Action?

580
00:37:28,266 --> 00:37:30,530
The ladies like that.
They never vote before.

581
00:37:30,701 --> 00:37:32,259
Fine.

582
00:37:35,740 --> 00:37:39,540
Higa Jiga. They say they want Higa Jiga.
She gonna make a classy president.

583
00:37:39,944 --> 00:37:41,605
I'm sure.

584
00:37:42,413 --> 00:37:43,573
What?

585
00:37:44,682 --> 00:37:47,446
Yes, I know. No, never mind.
I understand.

586
00:37:47,618 --> 00:37:50,519
Tell her I'll get her a helmet too.
Yeah, all right, fine.

587
00:37:50,688 --> 00:37:53,987
Yes, fine, all right. Fine. Now, now.

588
00:37:54,158 --> 00:37:55,716
I've been talking a long time.

589
00:37:55,893 --> 00:38:00,592
Folks, I'll bet you there are questions
you'd like to ask me. Ask them, Sakini.

590
00:38:07,438 --> 00:38:09,929
Oh, she say, "What time it is?" boss.

591
00:38:10,107 --> 00:38:12,473
Time? It's quarter to 5. Why?

592
00:38:12,643 --> 00:38:16,044
Oh, they got to go then, boss.
They not want to miss sunset.

593
00:38:16,214 --> 00:38:19,911
Every afternoon they like to go sit
in the pine grove and sip tea...

594
00:38:20,084 --> 00:38:21,551
...watch the sun go down.

595
00:38:21,719 --> 00:38:25,314
Isn't that nice. All right, Sakini,
you thank them all for me and tell them...

596
00:38:25,490 --> 00:38:29,654
...they can go to the pine grove and
sip tea and watch the sun go down.

597
00:38:34,131 --> 00:38:36,156
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

598
00:38:36,334 --> 00:38:37,926
Thank you very much.

599
00:38:38,102 --> 00:38:39,126
Thank you.

600
00:38:47,578 --> 00:38:48,806
How do you think we did?

601
00:38:48,980 --> 00:38:52,643
Oh, they cooperate, boss.
Future look very rosy.

602
00:38:52,817 --> 00:38:54,512
I wonder where I can find a cricket.

603
00:38:54,685 --> 00:38:57,153
Well, maybe have cricket
in your house now, not know.

604
00:38:57,321 --> 00:38:59,118
- I'll take these.
- Okay.

605
00:38:59,290 --> 00:39:01,349
- Thanks, Sakini.
- Sure.

606
00:39:01,526 --> 00:39:04,859
- I'll be right here you want me, boss.
- Right.

607
00:39:47,838 --> 00:39:49,305
Yes?

608
00:39:49,473 --> 00:39:51,771
- You busy, boss?
- No. What is it, Sakini?

609
00:39:51,943 --> 00:39:55,811
Boss, Mr. Sumata leave
a present for you.

610
00:39:55,980 --> 00:39:58,448
Put it on the shelf where it
will be out of the way.

611
00:39:58,616 --> 00:40:00,607
Not able to, boss, the present get mad.

612
00:40:00,785 --> 00:40:02,377
What?

613
00:40:06,991 --> 00:40:08,891
- Who's she?
- Souvenir.

614
00:40:09,060 --> 00:40:10,789
What...? What are you talking about?

615
00:40:10,962 --> 00:40:12,987
This the present from Mr. Sumata, boss.

616
00:40:13,164 --> 00:40:16,600
Introducing Lotus Blossom,
geisha girl first-class.

617
00:40:16,767 --> 00:40:20,100
America-san, Captain Fisby.

618
00:40:26,844 --> 00:40:29,938
She say she very happy
to belong to handsome captain.

619
00:40:30,114 --> 00:40:33,777
- She say she gonna serve you well.
- She's not gonna serve me at all.

620
00:40:33,951 --> 00:40:37,682
I want you to get your friend. I want
you to tell him I'm returning his gift.

621
00:40:37,855 --> 00:40:40,289
- Impossible to do, boss.
- Why?

622
00:40:40,458 --> 00:40:43,086
Mr. Sumata go to mountain, visit cousin.

623
00:40:43,260 --> 00:40:47,856
He leave present for you and
wish you very best success in Tobiki.

624
00:40:48,099 --> 00:40:49,657
What? What did she say?

625
00:40:49,834 --> 00:40:52,632
She said she want know where
you want her to stay, boss.

626
00:40:52,803 --> 00:40:57,069
I d... I don't care where she stays,
but she can't stay here.

627
00:40:57,241 --> 00:41:00,677
Where she go, boss?
She got no home now.

628
00:41:03,547 --> 00:41:06,641
- Look... Wait a minute.
- She want to put your kimono on for you.

629
00:41:06,817 --> 00:41:10,275
- She trained to please you.
- I know what she's trained to do.

630
00:41:10,454 --> 00:41:12,752
And I don't need any translation there.

631
00:41:12,923 --> 00:41:16,381
Now, you get my stuff
out of the supply shack...

632
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:19,791
...and you... You know,
and we'll put her up over there.

633
00:41:20,231 --> 00:41:23,496
Not very democratic, boss.
You make her lose face.

634
00:41:23,668 --> 00:41:26,831
- She think she bad geisha girl.
- I've got a bit of face to save.

635
00:41:27,004 --> 00:41:32,465
Now, don't give me any of that
Oriental hanky-panky business, you know.

636
00:41:38,082 --> 00:41:40,175
All right, what...? What's she saying?

637
00:41:40,351 --> 00:41:42,649
Oh, she say for me
to go home to grandpa, boss.

638
00:41:42,820 --> 00:41:44,879
She first-class geisha girl.

639
00:41:45,056 --> 00:41:47,149
She know her business.

640
00:41:47,458 --> 00:41:50,791
- Good night, boss.
- Sakini?

641
00:41:52,463 --> 00:41:55,864
This is all a big mistake. You kn...

642
00:41:56,267 --> 00:41:58,258
S... Sakini.

643
00:41:59,336 --> 00:42:01,270
- Me.
- Me.

644
00:42:01,439 --> 00:42:03,964
- Me, no.
- Me, no.

645
00:42:05,009 --> 00:42:07,204
No, this is not a kimono.
This is a bathrobe...

646
00:42:07,378 --> 00:42:10,404
...and I don't want to put it on, you see?

647
00:42:12,183 --> 00:42:13,912
Sakini!

648
00:42:14,518 --> 00:42:17,146
This is against regulations.

649
00:42:18,189 --> 00:42:19,247
Hello!

650
00:42:21,258 --> 00:42:24,125
You don't have to shout. I can hear you.

651
00:42:24,295 --> 00:42:27,992
- This is Colonel Purdy.
- Yes, sir.

652
00:42:28,165 --> 00:42:31,328
<i>Just thought I'd check up on you.
How are things going?</i>

653
00:42:31,502 --> 00:42:32,867
<i>Anything I can do for you?</i>

654
00:42:33,037 --> 00:42:35,164
I can't think of a thing, sir.

655
00:42:36,107 --> 00:42:39,975
<i>I realize it's bound to get
lonely for you down there.</i>

656
00:42:40,144 --> 00:42:42,009
<i>So you know
what I'm gonna do, my boy?</i>

657
00:42:42,179 --> 00:42:45,148
<i>- Now, what are you gonna do?
- I'll tell you.</i>

658
00:42:45,316 --> 00:42:48,877
<i>I'm gonna send you some of
my old Adventure magazines.</i>

659
00:42:49,053 --> 00:42:51,681
No, I don't want them.

660
00:42:51,856 --> 00:42:53,824
Thank you, sir.
Thank you, sir, very much.

661
00:42:53,991 --> 00:42:57,927
I would like something to read, sir.

662
00:42:58,095 --> 00:43:00,359
<i>How are you getting
along with the natives?</i>

663
00:43:00,531 --> 00:43:02,192
Well, it's an age-old problem, sir.

664
00:43:02,366 --> 00:43:06,496
It's a question... Or a struggle to see
who's going to lose face.

665
00:43:06,670 --> 00:43:08,001
<i>I understand.</i>

666
00:43:08,172 --> 00:43:12,939
As Mrs. Purdy says, "East is East, and
West is West and there can be no twain."

667
00:43:13,577 --> 00:43:15,204
<i>But you are making progress?</i>

668
00:43:15,379 --> 00:43:18,371
Well, nothing that I'd like
to put on paper, sir.

669
00:43:18,549 --> 00:43:21,712
<i>Well, send in a detailed progress report.</i>

670
00:43:21,886 --> 00:43:24,878
Well, if that's what
you'd like me to do, sir. Yes, sir.

671
00:43:25,055 --> 00:43:29,890
<i>You'll find that these people lack
the capacity for sustained endeavor.</i>

672
00:43:30,060 --> 00:43:32,028
<i>Don't hesitate to build a fire under them.</i>

673
00:43:32,196 --> 00:43:34,824
I don't think that that
will be necessary, sir.

674
00:43:34,999 --> 00:43:38,662
<i>Don't forget, the eyes of
Washington are on you, Fisby.</i>

675
00:43:38,836 --> 00:43:40,963
Oh, I hope not, sir.

676
00:43:41,739 --> 00:43:46,608
<i>It just occurred to me. Have you given
any thought to physical education?</i>

677
00:43:46,777 --> 00:43:49,177
Well, I don't think that...

678
00:43:49,346 --> 00:43:52,042
You know, sir, that was a
masterpiece of timeliness, sir.

679
00:43:52,216 --> 00:43:54,514
<i>Thank you, my boy.</i>

680
00:43:55,619 --> 00:43:57,814
<i>Could you use a deck of cards?</i>

681
00:43:58,856 --> 00:44:01,290
Sir, l...

682
00:44:03,527 --> 00:44:05,620
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

683
00:44:05,796 --> 00:44:08,060
<i>Fisby, you're getting weak.</i>

684
00:44:08,232 --> 00:44:10,257
No. No.

685
00:44:10,935 --> 00:44:13,563
Well, be good, my boy.

686
00:44:13,737 --> 00:44:15,364
